The Minister of Foreign Affairs and East African Cooperation, Prof Palamagamba Kabudi has assured Tanzania is supporting Burundi in its bid to join the Southern African Development Community (SADC). Prof Kabudi made revealed this at the Joint Permanent Commission for Cooperation meeting involving the two neigbouring country in Kigoma Region. He said Tanzania will continue to strengthen the fraternal ties between the two countries as one way to honour their founders. "The only way to honour the founders of the two nations is to strengthen relations in various fields including economic, social and security issues," Kabudi said. SADC has 16 members while its founders are Zimbabwe, Mozambique, Botswana, Angola, Tanzania, Zambia, Malawi, Lesotho and Eswatini.